'''Jacob Mikael Widell Zetterström''' (born 11 July 1998) is a Swedish professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for {{English football updater|DerbyCou}} club [[Derby County F.C.|Derby County]] and the [[Sweden men's national football team|Sweden national team]].

==Club career==
===Early career===
Widell Zetterström started his senior career in [[IFK Lidingö Fotboll|IFK Lidingö]], joining [[Djurgårdens IF Fotboll|Djurgårdens IF]] in 2019 and going on loan back to Lidingö the first season.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://fotbolltransfers.com/site/player/9405|title=35. Jacob Widell Zetterström|publisher=Fotbolltransfers|language=Swedish|access-date=23 May 2021}}</ref> Without having a place in the squad in 2020 due to a head injury, he made his Djurgården debut in 2021.<ref>{{Cite web |title=J. Widell Zetterström |url=https://int.soccerway.com/players/jacob-widell-zetterstrom/554201/ |access-date=1 August 2020 |website=Soccerway|publisher=Perform Group}}</ref> He would play 118 times for Djurgården.

===Derby County===
On 16 August 2024, Widell Zetterström signed with [[EFL Championship|English Championship]] club [[Derby County F.C.|Derby County]], on a three-year-contract after an undisclosed fee was agreed between Derby and Djurgården.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.derbytelegraph.co.uk/sport/football/transfer-news/derby-county-transfers-jacob-zetterstrom-9488541|title=Derby County confirm biggest transfer of the summer|publisher=DerbyshireLive|date=16 August 2024|access-date=16 August 2024}}</ref> Widell Zetterström made his Derby County debut in a 2–1 defeat to [[Watford F.C.|Watford]] on 24 August 2024.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.derbytelegraph.co.uk/sport/football/transfer-news/jacob-widell-zetterstroms-perfect-response-9508614|title=Jacob Widell Zetterstrom's perfect response to Watford fans as Derby County transfer need laid bare|publisher=DerbyshireLive|date=25 August 2024|access-date=29 August 2024}}</ref> Widell Zetterström established himself as Derby's first choice goalkeeper beating off competition from [[Josh Vickers]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.derbytelegraph.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/derby-county-winners-and-losers-9622127|title='Blimey' - the winners and the losers as brilliant Derby County defy early expectation
|publisher=DerbyshireLive|date=10 October 2024|access-date=11 October 2024}}</ref> Widell Zetterström's season came to a premature end in April 2025 with four games of the season remaining, after a facial injury picked up against [[Portsmouth F.C.|Portsmouth]], during the [[2024–25 Derby County F.C. season|2024–25 season]] he played 42 times for Derby, 40 times in the league with nine clean sheets as Derby finished 19th in the Championship.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://footballleagueworld.co.uk/john-eustace-confirms-derby-county-jacob-zetterstrom-injury-blow/|title=John Eustace confirms significant Derby County injury blow following Luton Town loss|publisher=Football League World|date=18 April 2025|access-date=14 May 2025}}</ref>

Widell Zetterström returned from injury ahead of the [[2025–26 Derby County F.C. season|2025–26 season]] and kept his place as first-choice goalkeeper. He was nominated for the [[EFL Championship Player of the Month]] for October 2025.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.derbytelegraph.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/derby-county-transfers-jacob-zetterstrom-10642543|title=Jacob Widell Zetterstrom stats prove Derby County value as he faces triple battle|publisher=Derby Telegraph|date=13 November 2025|access-date=27 January 2026}}</ref> Amid transfer speculation about a potential move to a [[Premier League]] club, it was reported in January 2026 that Widell Zetterström was in talks over a potential contact extension at Derby.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.derbytelegraph.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/derby-county-transfers-jacob-zetterstrom-10642543|title=Derby County 'interested in' Championship goalkeeper as contract 'in the pipeline'|publisher=Derby Telegraph|date=15 January 2026|access-date=27 January 2026}}</ref> In January 2026, Widell Zetterström was forced out of the Derby team with an viral infection. He was ruled out of action for February and March with Derby head coach [[John Eustace]] calling the mystery illness a "worrying" time for the player who suffered multiple concussions when playing in Sweden, he was sent for tests to investigate the issue.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/articles/c8jxxjkmzkdo|title='Worrying time' for virus-hit Zetterstrom - Eustace|publisher=BBC Sport|date=5 March 2025|access-date=13 March 2026}}</ref> Widell Zetterström return to action 18 April 2026 in a match against [[Oxford United F.C.|Oxford United]], after a three-month absence from the team.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.derbytelegraph.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/derby-county-jacob-widell-zetterstrom-10934155|title=Jacob Widell Zetterstrom opens up on Derby County injury return and 'what meant the world'
|publisher=Derby Telegraph|date=24 April 2026|access-date=30 April 2026}}</ref> His save from [[Scott Twine]]'s free-kick on 22 August 2025 against [[Bristol City F.C.|Bristol City]] was awarded Save of the Season at Derby County's end-of-season awards.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.dcfc.co.uk/news/2026/04/202526-awards-clarke-named-jack-stamps-player-of-the-season|title=2025/26 AWARDS: Clarke Named Jack Stamps Player of the Season|publisher=Derby County|date=28 April 2026|access-date=30 April 2026}}</ref> Widell Zetterström made 33 apperances for Derby County during his second season at the club, keeping seven clean sheets.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.dcfc.co.uk/news/2026/05/international-zetterstroem-selected-in-sweden-world-cup-squad|title=INTERNATIONAL CALL-UP: Zetterström Selected For Sweden World Cup Squad
|publisher=Derby County|date=12 May 2026|access-date=13 May 2026}}</ref>

==International career==
Widell Zetterström made his full international debut for [[Sweden men's national football team|Sweden]] on 12 January 2023, playing for 45 minutes before being replaced by [[Oliver Dovin]] in a [[Exhibition game|friendly]] 2–1 win against [[Iceland national football team|Iceland]].<ref name=":0">{{Cite web |title=Sverige - Island - Matchfakta - Svensk fotboll |url=https://www.svenskfotboll.se/matchfakta/sverige-island-landskamper-herr-senior/5387000/ |access-date=2023-01-13 |website=www.svenskfotboll.se |language=sv |archive-date=12 January 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230112201020/https://www.svenskfotboll.se/matchfakta/sverige-island-landskamper-herr-senior/5387000/ |url-status=dead }}</ref>

Widell Zetterström was named in Sweden's [[2026 FIFA World Cup]] squad.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/articles/ckgp3ekx98yo|title=Zetterstrom & Johansson in Sweden's World Cup squad
|publisher=BBC Sport|date=12 May 2026|access-date=13 May 2026}}</ref>

